onto the desk beside him, then turned in his chair to watch his sister. Cybel was covered in teddy bear stuffing, and torn limbs of half a dozen of of her toys. Prophet kept a good supply, if she didn't have them, she would destroy anything else she could get her hands on. &quot; Cybel, your running out of toys again Hun, you really should be nicer to your...&quot; Prophets words cut off, as he dodged a stuffed lion, missing its tail and front legs. Prophet sighed, and went to the closet, bringing out a box filled with new toys, and gave Cybel a few more. He sat down on the floor with her, and just put his arms around her as she rocked slowly back and forth and sang a child's song under her breath. Quietly, he spoke to her in a gentle tone.&quot; Cybel, I have to go out for a few, we need to feed, and its been a few days, you have to play with Chauncy a bit, he needs some love, but I will be back in an hour or so&quot; Cybel stopped rocking, her eyes brimmed with crimson tears as she said to him in a mere whisper &quot; not go out brother...you will die too, they all die, they all murder...your next I know they gonna kill you too maybe. they will kill me too they hate us, they hate us all...don't go brother you'll be dead, then I will die too&quot; the tears of blood streamed down her cheeks, staining the alabaster skin in rivulets of bloody sorrow. &quot; No Cybel, they wont come after me. I'm smart enough to steer clear of those fucks...but we wont last long holed up here in our little fortress. I will use the sewers, Lowry is down there too, he will watch my back. I will be right back, play with Chauncy, and call me on the 'puter if you really need me.&quot; Prophet left his sister as she played catch the shredded stuffed animal with Chauncy, the over grown ghouled alligator they kept as a pet. Prophet hit the sewers, and came up near the old abandon rail station, he made a few stops, watching things like he normally did, even though he wasn't scourge anymore. He saw a figure walking the length of the tracks, and with his heightened sense of vision, he could tell it was Simon, some random new vampire he knew about, hung with some creepy lame guy named Doctor Demento or something. Prophet let his thoughts wander, forgetting about Simon, and the city, and just focused on what he was going to do next. He had Cybel to take care of. He had to survive, so she could survive, simple as that. &quot;Politics, and assholes&quot; he whispered out loud,&quot; Why do they always come in pairs?&quot;<br>
Prophet hopped down off the loading dock, and thought about getting someone to feed Cybel. As he wandered down the darkened alley, the thought passed through his mind ' Some times I just want to Scream...it would be very calming'<br>
